document.queryselector("h1").innerhtml = "good morning";
        it converts the "h1" into the good morning.
        
=>it is always a good practice to add or link  external .js file at the end of the .html file.      

=========================
...................

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>css tutorial</title>
     <link rel="stylesheet" href="tutorial.css">
    <!-- this is type of external css -->
    <style>
       /* p{ */
            /* color:red; */
            /* background: rgb(153, 147, 153) !important; */ <!--the important is for more precedance-->
        /* } */
    </style>   overriding after link
    <!-- in between style is type of internal  css syntax  -->
</head>
<body>
    <h>this is a css tutorial</h>
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Optio, fugit.</p>
    <p style="color:red">Lorem ipsum dolor sit, amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nostrum voluptas esse pariatur.</p>
    <!-- it is a inline css -->
</body>
</html>

-->>>>in this we have first html then inside that head and body then inside head and body and so on......
the if we have to change "h" located inside the body then.....
--->>>>document.firstelementchild.lastelementchild.firstelementchild.innerhtml = "mahesh";













